Nigeria’s first and largest content market, C3 Africa, is back with an exclusive networking event which would announce the C3 Africa content markets across Africa for 2018 – 2019. The event will feature powerful and insightful keynote and panel sessions which would unveil the secrets to succeeding in the emerging industry. Opening Speaker: WELCOME TO NOLLYWOOD The event would be opened by the media veteran and guru
Obi Asika – Founder, Social Media Week. Key Note Speaker: AFRICAN CONTENT by AFRICA. Sam Onyemelukwe shares his personal journey, life hacks and growth as a business leader in the entertainment industry. Also speaking extensively on African made global content, distribution, regulation, piracy. Sam Onyemelukwe – MD, TRACE Nigeria. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-690384 size-large lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/square-1-1152x1152.jpg" alt="" width="1152" height="1152" /> Panel Session: CONTENT IS QUEEN Veteran women in the business of film & TV take centre stage as they share their vision for the industry, tackle hard topics and also speak on the light and dark side of the burgeoning industry. Panel Sessions: WOMEN BEHIND THE SCENES A focus on young women in the industry of Film and TV their experiences, their success and what the see as the future of the emerging industry alongside new projects. Meet The Cast of LARA & THE BEAT (Press Conference) Catch the amazing cast of LARA & THE BEAT the new sensational movie from the stable of Biola Alabi Media at the C3 Africa networking symposium at an all revealing press conference featuring lead actors and movie director. The event will close with laughter as comedian and actor Hafeez Oyetoro takes center stage and narrates the growth of the industry while naming calling the G.O.A.T.s (Greatest Of All Time) of the film industry both behind and in front of the Camera.